<div id="sub-main" >
	<div id="wiki-content-block">

	
		


<p><strong>Prism Stone</strong> is a Consumable in Dark Souls 3.</p> 
<div id="infobox" class="infobox"> 
 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;"> <h3>Prism Stone</h3> </td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/file/Dark-Souls-3/PrismStone.png" alt="" width="128"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td><br> 
      <blockquote> 
       <p>Warm pebble emitting a beautiful phasing aura of seven colors, with a very rare eighth.<br><br>The prism stone does nothing special, but can serve as a path marker, or perhaps dropped off a cliff to judge height by the sound of its descent. If a loud noise is heard upon its landing, then a fall from the ledge is surely lethal.</p> 
      </blockquote> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc0" class="bonfire"><a name="x--Green Blossom Usage"></a>Prism Stone Usage</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Toss to leave a colored light marker on the ground. Can take on a variety of different colors.</li> 
 <li>You can trade one of them to receive a <a class="wiki_link" href="/Twinkling+Titanite">Twinkling Titanite</a> at the <a class="wiki_link" title="crow" href="/Pickle+Pee,+Pump-a-Rum+Crow">crow</a> nest.</li> 
 <li>Prism stones laid on the ground before a player enters the world will not be visible to them.</li> 
 <li>Can be used to test if the height of a fall is Survivable.&nbsp; 
  <ul> 
   <li>When thrown off high ledges that the player can't survive with full HP (embered) or insta-kill chasms, It will give off a dying scream.</li> 
   <li>If it's a survivable fall, it will land on the ground and shine like normal.</li> 
   <li>It is Not fully accurate at low levels. Having minimal amounts of dexterity and vitality could cause the most risky falls to become lethal without making the prism stones alert you. (tested with 8 Vit, 12 Dex at some roof in High Wall of Lothric)</li> 
   <li>Fall damage is percentage-based, considering your max HP as embered, increases with equipped weight, and is reduced by your Vitality and Dexterity attributes.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc1" class="bonfire"><a name="x--Green Blossom Locations"></a>Prism Stone Locations</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Sold by <a class="wiki_link" href="/Shrine+Handmaid">Shrine Handmaid</a> for 10&nbsp;souls.</li> 
 <li>Dropped by ??</li> 
 <li>10x Found in the poison swamp of <a class="wiki_link" title="Farron Keep" href="/Farron+Keep">Farron Keep</a>, near the first bonfire.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 id="toc2" class="bonfire"><a name="x--Notes"></a>Notes</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Only 33 can be out at one time. If more are thrown down, the earliest stone will despawn.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
